				<div id="tab-2" class="tab-content">
					<h3>Recruiter</h3>
					<p>Our Recruiters are responsible for developing and maintaining relationships with the nation’s top IT talent that will aid our clients in technical contract-based projects or full-time opportunities. Compensation includes a competitive base salary and commission with high earning potential, performance bonuses, reward trip eligibility, health benefits, 401(k), and more. <strong>*A technology degree or experience is not necessary to be successful as a Recruiter or Sales Account Executive here at Brooksource.</strong></p>
					<h5>A day in the life of a Recruiter could include:</h5>
					<ul>
						<li>Using creative search avenues along with numerous recruiting tools, provided by Brooksource, to identify niche skilled candidates from various technical backgrounds across the country for technical upgrades, implementations and maintenance projects fora wide range of industries (i.e.healthcare, finance, retail, telecom, government, insurance and many more).</li>
						<li>Performing our due diligence to our clients to provide a full recruiting service; including, conducting thorough in-person interviews, reference/background checks and scheduling technical screens to ensure each candidate meets our professional expectations. Once the talent is identified,our recruiters add the Brooksource personal touch, by coaching the candidate through the on-site client interview process and facilitate a candidate/client introduction.</li>
						<li>Maintaining a relationship with candidates who become contractors working on-site at our clients. Brooksourcians uphold these relationships by consistently taking them out to lunch, hand delivering each contractor’s pay check weekly to the client site and touching base throughout the duration of their project.</li>
						<li>Attending networking events to continuously enhance your professional relationships within the IT industry</li>
					</ul>
					<p>Above all we are looking for leaders. We provide an un-paralleled, interactive training program lead by our top producers and corporate leaders. This will begin your continuous journey of professional and personal development. If you would like to be part of a fast paced, high growth organization, Brooksource is the best place to start and create a long lasting career.</p>
					<p>To learn more about our career opportunities and exciting culture visit <a href="www.brooksource.com/careers">www.brooksource.com/careers</a>.</p>
					<h5>What we seek in Brooksourcian:</h5>
					<ul>
						<li>Bachelor's degree</li>
						<li>Desire to learn and take initiative with a vision for personal & company growth</li>
						<li>Highly self-motivated and driven</li>
						<li>The innate ability to communicate and maintain positive energy in our open-pit environment</li>
					</ul>
					<h5>Locations:</h5>
					<p>Indianapolis, Detroit, Cincinnati, Columbus, Chicago, Louisville, Nashville, Philadelphia, Milwaukee, Charlotte, Denver, Atlanta, Hoboken, Jacksonville, Dallas, Minneapolis, Austin, St. Louis, Seattle, Grand Rapids and Hartford.</p>
